    "actions_taken": [
      "Worker evacuated to Terrebonne General in Houma, LA",
      "Incident verbally reported to BSEE NOD at 16:00 hours same day",
      "BSEE investigation initiated on September 23, 2020",
      "Daily reports, photos, and statements requested from H&P HSE representative"
    ],
    "summary": "On September 22, 2020 at approximately 14:30 hours, a floorhand injured his left ankle while descending a stairway at the Olympus N-88 rig (Shell Offshore facility) located at Mississippi Canyon 807 Platform B. The worker was carrying a seven-pound bucket of metal shavings while descending the northwest stairway to the shaker deck. He lost his footing on wet grating stair cover, stumbled approximately six steps, and landed awkwardly on his left leg. X-rays confirmed a left ankle fracture requiring surgery.",
